    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>E-ZPass for Passports?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jay M Pasachoff letter says government should set up passport applications bureaus in airports to deal with additional demand (Jan 23 article)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scrambling to Get Hold of a Passport'' (Business Day, Jan. 23):</p>
        <p>If the government were functional, it would set up temporary passport-application bureaus in airports, so people could apply on their way out of the country, or coming back in.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Scrambling to Get Hold of a Passport'' (Business Day, Jan. 23):</p>
        <p>If the government were functional, it would set up temporary passport-application bureaus in airports, so people could apply on their way out of the country, or coming back in.</p>
        <p>Why shouldn't the government go where the business is?</p>
        <p>Jay M. Pasachoff  Williamstown, Mass., Jan. 23, 2007</p>
      </block>
